# Session Logging & Decisions

Work happens in short, weekly sessions. `.cursor/notes/` keeps continuity between them.

## At the start of a session
- Read `.cursor/notes/session-log.md` and open the latest entry in `.cursor/notes/sessions/`.
- Continue from its "Next steps".

## At the end of a session (or a natural stopping point)
- Create a **new** file `.cursor/notes/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` (copy `sessions/TEMPLATE.md`).
- Keep it short - summarize, don't diff (git holds the diff). Fill in:
  - Date / timestamp
  - What changed (brief)
  - Current state / what's working
  - Open issues or blockers
  - Next steps / TODO
- Add a one-line link to the new entry at the top of the index in `session-log.md`.

## Decision records
When a non-trivial choice is made ("we chose X over Y because Z"), add a new file
`.cursor/notes/decisions/NNNN-<slug>.md` (copy `decisions/TEMPLATE.md`): context, decision,
alternatives considered, rationale, consequences.

## Rules
- These notes are committed to git; do not place secrets in them.
- One session entry per session; one decision record per decision.
